just_use show_board.py

# label: TOOL
# role: pretty-print a board for REPL / quick debugging

Prints one stack per line as space-separated card labels
(e.g. `5H 8C JS`). Used in tests, ad-hoc REPL sessions, and
narrated debugging output.

```python
import show_board
show_board.show(board)
```

## Pointers

- Companion: `feedback_board_display_format.md` — the canonical
  one-stack-per-line format Steve uses.
